    • selectSeat

      int selectSeat(Flight flight, AccountStatus accountLevel)
      Allows the user to select a seat after being provided a list of seats available to them.

      First calls viewAvailableSeats to display what seats the user can pick from. Prompts the user to select a seat, sets marks that seat as unavailable, and returns the seat number to the BookFlight method.

      Parameters:
      flight - The flight being booked
      accountLevel - The user account level
      Returns:
      The integer of the seat the user has selected
      See Also:
      • viewAvailableSeats(edu.mu.NorthEastAirlines.Flight)
